- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design and methodology of a literature review on open-source platforms, which falls under the domain of software engineering research. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the implications of past platform-wars on the current mobile devices platforms-war, which has societal and economic implications. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon the complexity of open-source platforms and their development. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the programming languages used in open-source platforms. 
- cs.CS (Computer Science) is a broad category that encompasses all aspects of computer science research, including software engineering, computational complexity, and programming languages, so it is also a possible category for this paper.
